The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 25 May is 42,133 (4,876.6 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 20 May, there were 43 new confirmed cases (5.0 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 13 May, there were 99 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 57% (56 fewer cases).
